/*!
\page handle_colorspec COLORSPEC Color Property Description

<p>
Section: \ref sec_handle "Handle-Based Graphics"
\section Usage
There are a number of ways of specifying a color value for
a color-based property.  Examples include line colors, 
marker colors, and the like.  One option is to specify
color as an RGB triplet
\verbatim
   set(h,'color',[r,g,b])
\endverbatim
where <tt>r,g,b</tt> are between @[0,1]@.  Alternately, you can
use color names to specify a color.
<UL>
<LI>  <tt>'none'</tt> - No color.
 </LI>
<LI>  <tt>'y','yellow'</tt> - The color @[1,1,0]@ in RGB space.
 </LI>
<LI>  <tt>'m','magenta'</tt> - The color @[1,0,1]@ in RGB space.
 </LI>
<LI>  <tt>'c','cyan'</tt> - The color @[0,1,1]@ in RGB space.
 </LI>
<LI>  <tt>'r','red'</tt> - The color @[1,0,0]@ in RGB space.
 </LI>
<LI>  <tt>'g','green'</tt> - The color @[0,1,0]@ in RGB space.
 </LI>
<LI>  <tt>'b','blue'</tt> - The color @[0,0,1]@ in RGB space.
 </LI>
<LI>  <tt>'w','white'</tt> - The color @[1,1,1]@ in RGB space.
 </LI>
<LI>  <tt>'k','black'</tt> - The color @[0,0,0]@ in RGB space.
 </LI>
</UL>
